By car, by train, by foot, thousands are descending on Kiev this week to mark a special anniversary.

But no ordinary train will do for Ukraine's religious leaders as they prepare to celebrate the 1,025th anniversary of the 'baptism of Kievan Rus' - the medieval kingdom that first witnessed the conversion of the region's pagans to Christianity.

A special armoured 'temple wagon' - kitted out with church fixtures, including a belfry and choir - has been laid on to transport Russian president Vladimir Putin, Russian Orthodox Church leader Patriarch Kirill and other dignitaries to mark the religious milestone.

