The customised five-carriage train contains a vestry in place of a conductor's compartment, an altar, lectern - and even a 50-litre container for run-off holy water.

It will also transport the X-shaped Cross of St Andrew the Apostle, which is on loan from its home cathedral in Patras, Greece.

'Prayer services will be held all the way down to Kiev,' a church spokesman told Ukrainian daily Segodnya.

Meanwhile, a railway source said the train is 'like a hotel on wheels' - albeit one decorated with gold leaf.

Putin, along with top clerics from the 15 national Eastern Orthodox churches, are due to arrive in the Ukrainian capital tomorrow.

